LEGB  =>  Local, Enclosing, Global, Built-in.
In this order python checks a variable scope.

local scope is scope of functions.

enclosing scope refers to scope nested functions where inner function scope is local and outer functions one is enclosing.

gloabal scope refers to scope top most scope outside of any thing.







TWO STATEMENT=======>


* global  => to change a variable of global scope from local scope.


* nonlocal => to change a variable from enclosing scope from local scope.
  (Used in case of nested functions)
